Uses of Class
rogel.io.fopl.formulas.operators.AbstractOperator

  • Packages that use AbstractOperator 
    Package Description
    rogel.io.fopl.formulas.operators
    Contains classes that implement the range of AbstractOperator Formulas.

    • Uses of AbstractOperator in rogel.io.fopl.formulas.operators

      Subclasses of AbstractOperator in rogel.io.fopl.formulas.operators 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  AndOperator
      An AndOperator is an AbstractOperator Formula that computes the logical conjunction of its constituent Formulas as its value.
      class  NotOperator
      A NotOperator is an AbstractOperator Formula that computes the logical opposite of its constituent Formula as its value.
      class  OrOperator
      An OrOperator is an AbstractOperator Formula that computes the logical disjunction of its constituent Formulas as its value.
      Methods in rogel.io.fopl.formulas.operators that return AbstractOperator 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      AbstractOperator OrOperator.getOperatorTail() 
      AbstractOperator NotOperator.getOperatorTail()
      Because the NotOperator cannot have a tail as defined by getOperatorTail(), this method always returns null.
      AbstractOperator AndOperator.getOperatorTail() 
      abstract AbstractOperator AbstractOperator.getOperatorTail()
      Constructs a new operator applied to this.operandCount() - 1 operands: the operands obtained by removing the operand Formula returned by this.getOperatorHead().
